<p>Please use the mailing lists, or #zftalk on freenode IRC for support.</p>

<p>With regard to why functionally this is not an issue:</p>

<p>The /m/c in your route will not be parameters, but only something which would have to be matched to use that route for the request.
if you wish those to be parameters, use the parameternaming to make them parameters.
:m/:c/* for example.</p>

